After implementation, verify:

- [ ] `POST /api/cli/deploy` with valid token and valid projectId returns 200 with deploymentId
- [ ] `POST /api/cli/deploy` with valid token and invalid projectId returns 404
- [ ] `POST /api/cli/deploy` without Authorization header returns 401
- [ ] `POST /api/cli/deploy` with invalid token returns 401
- [ ] `POST /api/cli/deploy` without projectId in body returns 400
- [ ] `GET /api/cli/env/:projectId?scope=production` returns env vars with secrets masked
- [ ] `GET /api/cli/env/:projectId?scope=preview` returns preview env vars
- [ ] `GET /api/cli/env/:projectId?scope=invalid` returns 400
- [ ] `POST /api/cli/env/:projectId` upserts vars and returns count
- [ ] `POST /api/cli/env/:projectId` with empty vars array returns 400
- [ ] Both routes return 404 for non-existent project IDs
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes with no errors in the dashboard package
